[<p class="sh2"><span>SIGN UP</span> FOR OUR NEWSLETTER</p>, <p><em>From the <a href="/web/20161028144519/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/10/26/the-media-is-priming-donald-trump-supporters-for-a-loss/">Washington Post</a>:</em></p>, <p class="sh2"><span>SIGN UP</span> FOR OUR NEWSLETTER</p>, <p>Since the final presidential debate last week, many news outlets have been delivering an unvarnished message to Donald Trump supporters: Your candidate is virtually\xa0certain to lose the election Nov. 8.</p>, <p>\u201c<a href="/web/20161028144519/http://fivethirtyeight.com/features/clinton-probably-finished-off-trump-last-night/">Clinton probably finished off Trump last night</a>,\u201d FiveThirtyEight founder Nate Silver wrote the day after the debate.\xa0\u201c<a href="/web/20161028144519/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/oct/20/hillary-clinton-president-debate-us-election">Hillary Clinton is almost certain to be president</a>,\u201d Guardian columnist and former New York Times executive editor Jill Abramson added.</p>, <p>A day later, the Times\u2019s Upshot blog <a href="/web/20161028144519/http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2016/upshot/presidential-polls-forecast.html?smid=tw-nytimes&amp;smtyp=cur#recent-state-changes">increased Clinton\u2019s chances of winning to 93 percent</a>, an all-time high.\xa0On Monday, Politico\u2019s Ben Schreckinger wrote that \u201c<a href="/web/20161028144519/http://www.politico.com/story/2016/10/clinton-trump-election-countdown-polls-230212#ixzz4O828qDMS">Donald Trump\u2019s path to an election night win is almost entirely closed</a>.\u201d Here at The Fix, Chris Cillizza and Aaron Blake wrote that \u201c<a href="/web/20161028144519/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/10/24/donald-trumps-chances-of-winning-are-approaching-zero/?tid=pm_politics_pop_b">Donald Trump\u2019s chances of winning are approaching zero</a>.\u201d</p>, <p>These are accurate, statistically sound statements. But they are something else, too. Declarations that Trump is highly unlikely to win also serve as counters to the Republican nominee\u2019s warning\xa0that the \u201crigged\u201d election could be \u201c<a href="/web/20161028144519/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/10/11/donald-trump-warns-that-other-communities-are-poised-to-steal-the-election/">stolen from us</a>.\u201d</p>, <p><em>Read the rest of the article <a href="/web/20161028144519/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/10/26/the-media-is-priming-donald-trump-supporters-for-a-loss/">here</a>.</em></p>]